re’ + <i>beorg</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Pembridge was born in 1260, in Castle-Pulverbatch, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Ralph de Pembridge II, was 32 and her mother, Lucy de Guildford, was 28. She married Sir John de Burley Earl of Broomcroft in 1276. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1303, in Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1260–1303":"1260–1303","1263–Male":"1263–Surnud","1252–Male":"1252–Surnud","1280–1358":"1280–1358","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1228–Male":"1228–Surnud","1232–Female":"1232–Surnud","1228":"1228","about 1280":"umbes 1280","1303":"1303","1358":"1358","1276":"1276","1232":"1232","1252":"1252","1263":"1263","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","Burley, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bromscroft Castle, Shropshire, England":"Castle-Pulverbatch, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Craven Arms, Shropshire, England":"Craven Arms, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1260–1303":"1260–1303","1263–Male":"1263–Kuollut","1252–Male":"1252–Kuollut","1280–1358":"1280–1358","1280